claims:
Claims 1. A method for wireless communication by a first apparatus, comprising: generating a sequence of packets for transmission to a second apparatus; determining, based on one or more criteria, whether to request the second apparatus to at least temporarily ignore missing packets from the sequence; and transmitting a message comprising an indication of the determination to the second apparatus. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein the determination is whether to request the second apparatus to ignore the missing packets for a period of time for at least one layer of the second apparatus or permanently ignore the missing packets for a plurality of layers of the second apparatus. 3. The method of claim 1, wherein the one or more criteria comprises at least one of: a priority of the missing packets or an amount of time that the sequence of packets has been stored in the first apparatus. 4. The method of claim 3, wherein the determination comprises determining to request the second apparatus to permanently ignore the missing packets for a plurality of layers of the second apparatus if at least one of: the priority of the missing packets is below a first threshold or the amount of time is above a second threshold. 5. The method of claim 4, wherein the first threshold is based on priority of one or more packets added to the generated sequence. 6. The method of claim 4, wherein: the plurality of layers comprise a radio link control (RLC) layer and a packet data convergence protocol (PDCP) layer; and the determination to request the second apparatus to permanently ignore the missing packets comprises a determination to request the second apparatus to permanently refrain from processing the missing packets during the RLC layer of the second apparatus and the PDCP layer of the second apparatus. 7. The method of claim 3, wherein the determination comprises determining to request the second apparatus to ignore the missing packets for a period of time for at least one layer of the second apparatus if the priority of the missing packets is above a threshold. 8. The method of claim 7, wherein the determination to request the second apparatus to ignore the missing packets for the period of time comprises a determination to request the second apparatus to ignore the missing packets for the period of time during at least one of a radio link control (RLC) layer of the second apparatus or a packet data convergence protocol (PDCP) layer of the second apparatus. 9. The method of claim 1, further comprising: transmitting one or more packets of the sequence to the second apparatus, wherein the one or more packets are after the missing packets in the sequence, and wherein the message is transmitted with the one or more packets. 10. The method of claim 9, wherein the message further comprises an indication of sequence numbers for the missing packets. 1 1. The method of claim 1, wherein the message further comprises an indication of the determination for at least one of a radio link control (RLC) layer of the second apparatus or a packet data convergence protocol (PDCP) layer of the second apparatus. 12. The method of claim 11 , wherein the message further comprises an indication of at least one of RLC sequence numbers for the missing packets or PDCP sequence numbers for the missing packets. 13. The method of claim 1, further comprising: transmitting the sequence of packets to the second apparatus, wherein the message further comprises an indication of one or more links in which different portions of the sequence were transmitted. 14. The method of claim 13, wherein: the one or more links comprises one or more radio access technologies (RATs); and the one or more RATs comprises at least one of 4G, 5G or WIFI. 15. A method for wireless communication by a first apparatus, comprising: detecting one or more packets that are missing from a sequence of packets received from a second apparatus; receiving a request to at least temporarily ignore the missing packets when processing the sequence of packets; and processing the sequence of packets in accordance with the request. 16. The method of claim 15, wherein the request further comprises an indication of sequence numbers for the missing packets. 17. The method of claim 15, wherein the request further comprises an indication to at least temporarily ignore the missing packets during at least one of a radio link control (RLC) layer of the first apparatus or a packet data convergence protocol (PDCP) layer of the first apparatus. 18. The method of claim 17, wherein the request further comprises an indication of at least one of RLC sequence numbers for the missing packets or PDCP sequence numbers for the missing packets. 19. The method of claim 17, wherein the request comprises one of a first request to ignore the missing packets for a period of time for at least one of the RLC layer or the PDCP layer or a second request to permanently ignore the missing packets for both the RLC layer and the PDCP layer. 20. The method of claim 19, wherein: the request comprises the first request; and processing the sequence of packets comprises: 

 ignoring the missing packets for the period of time while performing PDCP reordering for one or more packets of the sequence, wherein the one or more packets are after the missing packets in the sequence; and after performing the PDCP reordering, sending the reordered packets to a higher layer of the first apparatus. 21. The method of claim 20, further comprising: after sending the reordered packets to the higher layer, receiving retransmitted packets corresponding to the missing packets; performing PDCP reordering for the retransmitted packets; and sending the reordered retransmitted packets to the higher layer of the first apparatus. 22. The method of claim 19, wherein: the request comprises the second request; and processing the sequence of packets comprises: refraining from sending a request for retransmission of the missing packets; and permanently ignoring the missing packets while performing PDCP reordering for one or more packets of the sequence of packets, wherein the one or more packets are after the missing packets in the sequence. 23. The method of claim 15, further comprising: receiving an indication of one or more links in which different portions of the sequence of packets were transmitted, wherein the processing of the sequence of packets is further based on the indicated one or more links. 24. The method of claim 23, wherein: the one or more links comprises one or more radio access technologies (RATs); and the one or more RATs comprises at least one of 4G, 5G or WIFI. 25. An apparatus for wireless communication, comprising: means for generating a sequence of packets for transmission to a device; 

 means for determining, based on one or more criteria, whether to request the device to at least temporarily ignore missing packets from the sequence; and means for transmitting a message comprising an indication of the determination to the device. 26. The apparatus of claim 25, wherein: the means for determining determines whether to request the device to ignore the missing packets for a period of time for at least one layer of the device or permanently ignore the missing packets for a plurality of layers of the device; and the one or more criteria comprises at least one of: a priority of the missing packets or an amount of time that the sequence of packets has been stored in the apparatus. 27. The apparatus of claim 26, wherein the means for determining: determines to request the device to permanently ignore the missing packets for a plurality of layers of the device if at least one of: the priority of the missing packets is below a first threshold or the amount of time is above a second threshold; or determines to request the device to ignore the missing packets for a period of time for at least one layer of the device if the priority of the missing packets is above the first threshold. 28. An apparatus for wireless communication, comprising: means for detecting one or more packets that are missing from a sequence of packets received from a device; means for receiving a request to at least temporarily ignore the missing packets when processing the sequence of packets; and means for processing the sequence of packets in accordance with the request. 29. The apparatus of claim 28, wherein the request further comprises an indication to at least temporarily ignore the missing packets during at least one of a radio link control (RLC) layer of the apparatus or a packet data convergence protocol (PDCP) layer of the apparatus. 30. The apparatus of claim 29, wherein the request comprises one of a first request to ignore the missing packets for a period of time for at least one of the RLC layer or the PDCP layer or a second request to permanently ignore the missing packets for both the RLC layer and the PDCP layer.
